<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LIFT AXLE SYSTEMS - TESTING AND TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl14019040">
        <title>TESTING AND TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The operational test,
                <hotlnk xrefid="t14019r">TABLE 1</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t14019r"/>, is used to verify that the lift axle is operating correctly. It may also be
                used to identify or verify the symptom of a malfunctioning lift axle. The symptom list,
                <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019b">TABLE 2</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t14019b"/>, provides a shortcut to troubleshooting when a symptom is known. The
                troubleshooting tables provide procedures for each of the symptoms identified in tables 1 and 2.
            </para>
            <para>A fault in the lift axle system will be apparent when the OPERATIONAL TEST cannot be completed
                successfully, or when a fault symptom is reported during normal system operation. If the fault is
                discovered while performing the operational test, refer to the troubleshooting table indicated in the
                failed step. If a fault symptom is known, locate the symptom in
                <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019b">TABLE 2</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t14019b"/>, and refer to the indicated troubleshooting table.
            </para>
            <para>Three types of faults are possible in the lift axle system: electrical, air, and mechanical. While
                troubleshooting an electrical problem, unless instructed otherwise, refer to FIGURES 41 through 51. When
                troubleshooting an air system problem, unless instructed otherwise, refer to FIGURE 10 or FIGURE 19.
                When troubleshooting a mechanical problem, refer to the table of contents to locate the section of the
                manual covering the axle configuration being tested.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Operational Test</title>
            <para>Table 1 is the Operational Test. This procedure can be run to identify a fault if no symptom is known.
                The same procedure is run after repairs to verify that the system is operating correctly.
            </para>
            <table id="t14019r" tblwidth="full-page">
                <title>Operational Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="6">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col5" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col6" colwidth="0.91in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col7" colwidth="1.30in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>OFF</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Set all lift axle UP/DOWN switches to UP.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE ENABLE switch must remain unlit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019s">TABLE 3</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019s"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col2"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col3"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>All lift axles must be in the UP position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                                <note>
                                    <para>After a truck has sat for several days, it is normal for the lift axle tires
                                        to be resting on the ground in the lowered position. This is due to the air
                                        system leaking down and does not indicate a problem as long as the lift axles
                                        return to the raised position once the truck is started and the air system is
                                        fully charged. (Verify after next step.)
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019t">TABLE 4</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019t"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Start engine and verify that air system is fully charged. Perform test with engine
                                    idling unless instructed otherwise.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <note>
                                    <para>If the AXLE ENABLE switch has been turned ON after the key was turned on, the
                                        conditions must be reset by cycling the key off for several seconds, then back
                                        on, before performing this step.
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                                <seqlist>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Place the transmission in PARK or NEUTRAL until instructed otherwise.
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Do not press the AXLE ENABLE switch (the lift axle system must be OFF).
                                        </para>
                                    </item>
                                </seqlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE ENABLE switch must remain unlit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019u">TABLE 5</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019u"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Turn on the lift axle system by momentarily pressing the AXLE ENABLE rocker
                                    switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE ENABLE switch must be lit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019v">TABLE 6</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019v"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col2"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col3"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>All lift axles must remain in the up position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019a">TABLE 13</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019a"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Set AXLE 1 UP/DOWN switch to DOWN.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE 1 UP/DOWN switch must be lit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Lift axle 1 must lower to the down position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019w">TABLE 7</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019w"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>While monitoring the gauge, slowly rotate the pressure regulator for lift axle 1
                                    clockwise to increase the operating pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>Verify that the following operating pressure can be reached and maintained, as
                                    indicated on the gauge located next to the pressure regulator.
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Fixed axles - 15 psi</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Self-Steering axles - 31 psi</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019x">TABLE 8</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019x"/>
                                    .
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If the system has two gauges per axle (mixed control systems), have a second
                                    person monitor the second gauge while rotating the regulator counter-clockwise to
                                    lower the pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>Verify that the second gauge reading tracks the first gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                                <note>
                                    <para>Leave the AXLE 1 UP/DOWN switch in the DOWN position.</para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019ab">TABLE 12</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019ab"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <note>
                                    <para>Single lift axle systems, proceed to step 16.</para>
                                </note>
                                <para>On systems with multiple lift axles, set AXLE 2 UP/DOWN switch to DOWN.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE 2 UP/DOWN switch must be lit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Lift axle 2 must lower to the down position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019y">TABLE 9</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019y"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>While monitoring the gauge, slowly rotate the pressure regulator for lift axle 2
                                    clockwise to increase the operating pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>Verify that the following operating pressure can be reached and maintained, as
                                    indicated on the gauge located next to the pressure regulator.
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Fixed axles - 15 psi</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Self-Steering axles - 31 psi</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019x">TABLE 8</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019x"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If the system has two gauges per axle (mixed control systems), have a second
                                    person monitor the second gauge while rotating the regulator counter-clockwise to
                                    lower the pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>Verify that the second gauge reading tracks the first gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019ab">TABLE 12</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019ab"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Set AXLE 2 UP/DOWN switch to UP.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <note>
                                    <para>Systems with two lift axles, proceed to step 16.</para>
                                </note>
                                <para>On systems with three lift axles, set AXLE 3 UP/DOWN switch to DOWN.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE 3 UP/DOWN switch must be lit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Lift axle 3 must lower to the down position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019z">TABLE 10</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019z"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>13.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>While monitoring the gauge, slowly rotate the pressure regulator for lift axle 3
                                    clockwise to increase the operating pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>Verify that the following operating pressure can be reached and maintained, as
                                    indicated on the gauge located next to the pressure regulator.
                                </para>
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Fixed axles - 15 psi</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Self-Steering axles - 31 psi</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019x">TABLE 8</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019x"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>14.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>If the system has two gauges per axle (mixed control systems), have a second
                                    person monitor the second gauge while rotating the regulator counter-clockwise to
                                    lower the pressure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <para>Verify that the second gauge reading tracks the first gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019ab">TABLE 12</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019ab"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>15.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Set AXLE 3 UP/DOWN switch to UP.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>16.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <note>
                                    <para>Fixed lift axle systems, proceed to step 18.</para>
                                </note>
                                <para>Systems with self-steering lift axles, perform steps 16 and 17.</para>
                                <seqlist>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Shift the transmission into REVERSE.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </seqlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Lift axle 1 must raise to the up position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE 1 UP/DOWN switch must be unlit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE ENABLE switch must be unlit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019aa">TABLE 11</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019aa"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>17.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Shift the transmission into PARK or NEUTRAL.</para>
                                <para>Lift axle 1 will lower to the DOWN position.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5"></entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Continue to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7"></entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>18.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>ON/OFF</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Turn the ignition key to the OFF position.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col5">
                                <randlist type="bullet">
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Lift axle 1 must return to the up position.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE 1 UP/DOWN switch must be unlit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>
                                        <para>Indicator on AXLE ENABLE switch must be unlit.</para>
                                    </item>
                                </randlist>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Operational Test successfully completed.</para>
                                <important>
                                    <para>Set all lift axle UP/DOWN switches to the UP position.</para>
                                </important>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col7">
                                <para>Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s14019_14.xml" xrefid="t14019s">TABLE 3</hotlnk>
                                    <xref refid="t14019s"/>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Assumptions:</para>
                                <para>The air compressor and air supply reservoir are operating within normal limits,
                                    and are fully charged throughout the procedure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
